 counts are weak; previous worktree files becoming committed files is strong; explicit links win.\n\n9. **Failure behavior**\n   Once GitMeta atomic `SetValue` exists, this is mostly solved. Still need to say capture fails the whole write if snapshot collection fails, or whether env snapshot is best-effort. I’d make transcript capture primary and env snapshot best-effort with an `environment_error` field only if we’re comfortable storing that.\n\nThe next best conversation is probably #2 and #5: exact snapshot JSON and index shape. Those drive the implementation more than the philosophy now.","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T01:33:06.814Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","phase":"final_answer"}}}